s in agent guidance. It mentions no required environment properties, and that tests can target offline APIs to avoid needing a live server, which is good news. I wonder if I should state that no action is required in this case. If there's no action, maybe I should keep the guidance concise and address potential risks. Also, I should think about how the driver interacts with properties and any necessary docker preparations for Neo4j testing.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating test requirements**\\n\\nI've noticed that existing tests are offline and one is failing due to a behavior change in version 5.28.8. It seems that the \\\"normal generated test scaffold\\\" is probably based on those existing tests. I need to decide if the library requires additional setup beyond the normal scaffold to ensure meaningful coverage. Even without Docker, I can still cover values and mapping effectively. However, the documentation states that normal usage needs a database for end-to-end driver testing, so that's something to keep in mind.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"no_action\",\n  \"summary\": \"No extra setup is concretely required. The resolved Neo4j Java Driver artifact brings its needed transitive dependencies, ships its own native-image properties, and existing meaningful coverage is reachable through offline value/mapping APIs without a live Neo4j server.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No required environment variables or system properties. Prefer offline tests around Values, Value.as(...), mapping annotations, temporal/list/value types, and driver configuration paths unless a test deliberately exercises real Bolt query execution.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Documentation examples normally connect to bolt://localhost:7687, so tests that exercise actual query execution would need an explicit Neo4j server, but that is not required for the current java-run failure or for meaningful offline reachability coverage.\",\n    \"The artifact includes native-image properties for Netty (-Dio.netty.noUnsafe=true and leak detection disabled); these are packaged with the jar and do not require separate test setup.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0a1c27fea242fd67016a429036ed208196b461459f86f90677\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1416, "output": 736, "cacheRead": 27136, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 29288, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782747180108, "responseId": "resp_0a1c27fea242fd67016a42902ca9dc819688bce5de0588ac5c"}}
